sent away to study at the Tower Skycleave at considerable personal expense. He
tells you how his son was the first person in the family to show any talent
for magic in generations, even if it wasn't much.
   At first, Dylane's son sent letters home to the family. In them, he always
wrote of being happy, but something always seemed wrong.
   'And then, one day, the letters just stopped,' says Dylane. 'We wrote and
wrote, with no response. The sorcerers won't speak to me. Nobody will help me.
I'm not allowed upstairs. Please, I'm just a father in search of my son. Please
find any sign of him. I pray he is okay.'
